Package: pleiotest
Title: Fast Sequential Pleiotropy Test
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c( person(given = "Fernando", family = "Aguate", role =
        c("aut", "cre"), email = "fmaguate@gmail.com", comment =
        c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3608-8425")),
        person(given = "Gustavo", family = "de los Campos", role =
        "aut", email = "gustavoc@msu.edu", comment = c(ORCID =
        "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5692-7129")), person(given =
        "Alexander", family = "Grueneberg", role = "ctb", email =
        "cran@agrueneberg.info") )
Description: It performs a fast multi-trait genome-wide association
        analysis based on seemingly unrelated regressions. It tests for
        pleiotropic effects based on a series of Intersection-Union
        Wald tests. The package can handle large and unbalanced data
        and plot results.
